      "setup_note": "Added a self-contained renderer-smoke package under experiments/main/run-angiostress-s0s1-renderer-smoke in the active idea worktree. The config points to the previously verified TopCoW volume/mask paths and uses a fixed seed. The script projects the 3D mask to a 256x256 DSA-like clean image, exports a projected GT mask, and creates three stressor families with three severity levels each.",
      "metric_summary": "topcow_resencm_one_case_mean_dice=0.6985; topcow_resencm_one_case_mean_cldice=0.6285; angiostress_renderer_success=1; angiostress_renderer_cell_count=9; angiostress_renderer_deterministic_hash_match=1; angiostress_renderer_projected_gt_area_pixels=8233",
      "result_summary": "The renderer-smoke pass generated 9 stressor cells across frame thinning, contrast phase, and device overlay. Required outputs were present; the projected GT area was 8,233 pixels with 2 connected components; clean GT self Dice and self clDice were both 1.0; all numeric metrics were finite; fresh rerun output hashes and per-cell hashes matched. Frozen 2D model inference was not run in this scoped pass and is recorded as deferred.",
      "impact_summary": null,
